The National Drug Law Enforcement Agency (NDLEA), Rivers State has arrested a physically challenged female for allegedly being in possession of 24 sacks of 231.2kgs of cannabis sativa. Mr Emmanuel Ogbumgbada, the Assistant Commander, Media and Advocacy (NDLEA), State Command in Port Harcourt confirmed her arrest to NAN. He stated that the NDLEA operatives conducted a search operation in Oyigbo Local Government Area of the State. Ogbumgbada said, ”We arrested one Celina Ekeke, a notorious drug dealer, with 24 sacks of cannabis sativa weighing 231.2kgs. ”She has been on the watch list of NDLEA for some time now as she uses her deformed legs to disguise and sell illicit drugs. “The suspect is presently under investigation at the Rivers Command headquarters.” He reiterated warning to all drug dealers to desist from the nefarious act as they would surely be fished out.